FBIS4-30729 "dreeu104_h_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-104 Daily Report 29 May 1994 HUNGARY Views Minorities in Neighboring States Views Minorities in Neighboring States LD2905182094 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 1730 GMT 29 May 94 LD2905182094 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network Slovak BFN [Text] Gyula Horn, leader of the Hungarian Socialist Party, who is the most likely candidate for the post of future Hungarian prime minister, said that the next Budapest government will advocate cultural autonomy for national minorities in neighboring states. In cases where a Hungarian minority is in effect a majority, the Hungarian Socialist chairman proposes administrative autonomy. This does not mean, however, we will be seeking to entice Hungarian minorities in neighboring states to strive for territorial autonomy or even separation, Horn added.
